  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Priyansh, that cricket joke mishap sounds tough — balancing fun and professionalism is tricky. Did you find a way to smooth it over?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yeah, I tried to laugh it off and said it was a \"cultural learning moment.\" My team is pretty chill, so they didn't take it seriously. But still, I'm extra careful now. 😅"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Laughing it off is smart — and 'cultural learning moment' is a smooth phrase. I get that extra careful feeling. How are meetings going these days?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Meetings are better. I try to speak slowly and use simple words. Sometimes I get stuck, but my manager helps me. It’s a slow but good progress. 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Slow progress is still progress. Speaking clearly takes practice. What’s one thing you feel more confident about now?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I’m more confident using technical terms in meetings. Before, I avoided them, but now I use them with examples. It makes my points clearer. Also, people nod more! 😄 But I still get nervous when I speak first."
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"That’s a great step forward — using examples helps a lot. Nervousness when speaking first is normal. What helps you calm down in those moments?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I take deep breaths and remind myself that it’s okay to take time. Sometimes I think, \"It's mein zimmedar hone ka hissa hai (part of being responsible).\" But still, my heart beats fast! 😅"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Taking deep breaths is a strong tool — and that Hindi reminder shows you’re tying confidence to values. Heartbeats calm with time. What’s one small win you’d like to celebrate soon?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I want to celebrate when I lead a meeting without notes. Just speaking clearly and letting my ideas flow. It feels close, but I want to practice more. Maybe next week? Let’s see. 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"That’s a solid goal — leading without notes shows growth. Practice makes progress. How do you plan to prepare for it?\""
    }
  ],
